 manager where he was responsible for two companies within the group involved in telecommunicationsrelated projects in may  dato’ abdul rahman founded cmc engineering to offer full turnkey engineering services relating to public transportation system telecommunications network rollout and oil and gas electrical and automation worksdato’ abdul rahman graduated with a diploma in electrical engineering communication from universiti teknologi malaysia in december  and subsequently obtained a bachelor of science degree in electronic and electrical engineering in july  from robert gordon university formerly known as robert gordon’s institute of technology in scotland united kingdom he also completed the stanfordnus executive program in february  zimin qian mr qian zimin is chief executive officer of the company he is the director of yinda pte ltd a wholly­owned subsidiary of shanghai yinda science and technology industrial co ltd shanghai yinda mr qian zhongcheng is also a director and  shareholder of shanghai yinda yinda pte ltd will be making a mandatory unconditional cash offer for all the ordinary shares in the capital of the company phua cher phua mr phua cher phua is an executive director of the company kevin phua is responsible for the overall management of our group’s business and corporate development and he works together with our nonexecutive chairman to formulate the business and corporate policies and strategies of our group he started his career in august  as an engineer with national semiconductor manufacturing pte ltd before he joined infineon technologies asia pacific pte ltd formerly known as siemens components pte ltd from march  to december  where he was involved in developing software for the testing of microchips as a senior engineer in january  kevin phua joined st assembly and test services pte ltd as an engineering section manager where he was incharge of testing microchips at its test development centre he subsequently joined flextronics international ltd in june  as a manager at its test development department where he was a division head and responsible for testing of product designs for singapore malaysia and china kevin phua founded and was the chief executive officer of nexfrontier solutions pte ltd from june  to september  prior to being appointed as our executive director and ceo kevin phua had been an executive director special function at tee international since october  and was involved in the executive and management role in the telecommunication operation infrastructure and information technology functions and merger and acquisition projects he will cease to hold any executive position at tee international or its group of companies following the listing of our company on the catalist kevin phua graduated from nanyang technological university with a bachelor of engineering degree in may  and from the national university of singapore with a master of science electrical engineering degree in july  kwee yee teo hazwan alif mr hazwan alif has been redesignated as the nonexecutive director of the company he primarily oversees the business development and administration functions of our group he began his career as an associate with kpmg in london between october  and july  when he was involved in the execution of full audit work on design and effectiveness of internal controls and statutory audit on financial statements hazwan alif joined ernst and young kuala lumpur malaysia between october  and july  as a senior associate where he led audit and nonaudit engagement teams serving a portfolio of clients including various banks and finance houses assetinvestment management firms and unit trust funds in july  he joined cmc engineering as the head of strategic development and focused on business strategy development and execution establishment of key collaborations between the company including our operations and its various partners he was also responsible for identifying opportunities for the company’s overseas expansions he will cease to hold any executive position at cmc engineering or its group of companies following the listing of our company on the catalist hazwan alif graduated from the university of warwick with a bachelor of science with honours degree in economics in july  he is an associate with the institute of chartered accountants in england and wales an affiliate of the institution of railway signal engineers and a committee member of the board of the institution of railway signal engineers malaysian section berhad geok soon sim mr sim geok soon is nonexecutive director of the company since  july  and is our nonexecutive director sim geok soon has more than  years of experience in the field of mechanical and electrical engineering sim geok soon started his career as an electrical technician in soon meng electrical engineering  plumbing contractors between october  and february  in march  sim geok soon joined link automation pte ltd as an electrical foreman where he was responsible for electrical installation from april  to may  sim geok soon worked as an assistant project engineer of lknes sea pte ltd to handle electrical work for various sewage pumping stations between may  and may  sim geok soon was posted to work on the phase a mass rapid transit project where he was a project engineer in kandenko co ltd he was subsequently assigned to work on the phase a mass rapid transit project as a project engineer in indeco engineering pte ltd between may  and may  in june  sim geok soon joined lindeteves jacoberg fe private limited as a project engineer before he left as a project manager in april  he was in charge of various water and waste projects in singapore and malaysia in april  he joined trans equatorial engineering pte ltd as a project director and later rose to the position of senior project directorexecutive director before he was promoted to managing director special projects he is in charge of mechanical and electrical engineering and special projects in singapore and overseas as well as project and construction management in the construction engineering industries he is also responsible for the business development duties of the company jakob hinrichsen mr jakob hinrichsen is nonexecutive independent director of the company since  july  he started his career with dsc communications dedicom as a project and service manager in july  he then served as the sales manager of tdc from june  to may  before he became the head of networks at energis carrier services in june  in november  jakob hinrichsen cofounded oghma and became its market development strategy and operations director where he was in charge of the development of business model market research and development of growth strategy for asia between october  and june  he served as a general manager of natrindo telepon seluler where he was responsible for strategy development and business planning for the company’s international business in october  jakob hinrichsen joined pt excelcomindo pratama xl as its vice president of corporate strategy and business development where he was responsible for strategy formation and execution of strategic initiatives in september  he became a senior vice president of corporate strategy and business transformation at pt xl axiata where he assisted the company in strategy formation and execution of strategic initiatives since october  jakob hinrichsen has also been the managing director of t hagen partners pte ltd an independent consultancy firm specialising in strategy formation and execution of growth strategies for companies in the internet communication and technology sectors in asia he is a member of the singapore institute of directors jakob hinrichsen graduated with a master of science in engineering degree from technical university of denmark in july  and a masters of business administration degree from insead in december  yee kit hong mr yee kit hong is nonexecutive lead independent director of the company since  july  prior to joining ernst  young in july  he worked as a project accountant in morrison knudsen low keng huat and as an accountant in brown  roots as well as an audit senior in wilson green  gibbs he was an assurance and tax manager at ernst  young when he left in september  since october  yee kit hong has been a partner at kit yee  co a firm providing audit accountancy and taxation advice or related services he is a principal partner responsible for providing assurance advisory consultancy and taxation services to clients yee kit hong is a member of the institute of chartered accountants in england and wales and a fellow of the institute of singapore chartered accountants he is also admitted as an accredited tax practitioner by the singapore institute of accredited tax professionals and a full member of the singapore institute of directors yee kit hong graduated with a bachelor of accountancy degree from university of singapore in june  alex siow mr alex siow is nonexecutive independent director of the company since  july  he started his career as a structural engineer in june  at the housing  development board where he was responsible for the design and construction of public housing in singapore and was promoted to head of the construction technology unit in april  where he was responsible for the introduction of several technologies for improvement of construction productivity in september  he was promoted to chief information officer responsible for the overall implementation of information technology to facilitate product development and customer service in march  alex siow joined starhub ltd as vice president of strategic relations and government affairs in the chief executive officer’s office before he was appointed as head of corporate sales in february  where he was responsible for the sales of all starhub products to the enterprise sector in february  he was promoted to head of business excellence and systems technology responsible for network convergence and the implementation of a new business support system in march  alex siow joined accenture pte ltd as managing director of health and public service in july  where he was responsible for sales origination of system integration and consultancy projects in the healthcare and public sectors in january  he joined national university of singapore as a professor in the department of information systems school of computing he is also the director of strategic technology management institute at national university of singapore alex siow graduated with a bachelor of engineering civil degree from stuttgart institute of technology in july  and a master of science engineering construction management degree from the university of birmingham in december  clifton yong mr mclifton yong is nonexecutive independent director of the company since  july  he began his career at the ministry of defence from june  to november  from may  to february  clifton yong was with nortel networks before he left as vice president of submarine cables and global carriers division responsible for the company’s optical portfolio in the submarine segment and coleading the global submarine networks initiatives which included manufacturing as well as research and development he then joined alcatel singapore in february  as managing director and left in march  as senior vice president of the asia pacific region responsible for the expansion of the company’s business into enterprises and vertical markets subsequently from march  to july  clifton yong was the chief commercial officer and group executive vice president of mediacorp pte ltd responsible for all commercial functions such as sales marketing operations and customer engagement functions he is currently the executive chairman of nano equipment pte ltd having successfully transformed the company from a technology system integrator to a cloudbased mobile solution provider concurrently he is also the managing director of the asia pacific region of kaltura inc a cloud hosting technology provider in asia pacific that is based in the united states of america clifton yong graduated from the national university of singapore with a bachelor of engineering electrical degree in july  and obtained a master of business administration general management degree from university of hull in april  he also completed the general manager program at harvard business school in november  basic compensation name fiscal year total abdul rahman  zimin qian  phua cher phua  kwee yee teo  hazwan alif  geok soon sim  jakob hinrichsen  yee kit hong  alex siow  clifton yong  as of  options compensation name options value abdul rahman   zimin qian   phua cher phua   kwee yee teo   hazwan alif   geok soon sim   jakob hinrichsen   yee kit hong   alex siow   clifton yong   insider trading » full list on insider trading related topics stocksstock screenermarket datatelecommunications servicesintegrated telecommunications services about our site cmc limited information cmc limited is now tata consultancy services about us cmc is now part of the  billion tata group asias largest global software services company with over  employees worldwide prior to the merger tata consultancy services limited tcs ltd was a strategic partner of cmc and worked to target the global market with additional offerings that leveraged the combined strengths of both companies recent articles information about ebiz inc what was cmc americas inc  cmcltdcom  cmc limited  privacy policy  august   cmc company  wikipedia cmc company from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from cmc limited jump to navigation search for other uses see cmc disambiguation cmc limited type subsidiary industry it services it consulting founded  december  headquarters new delhi india key people n chandrasekaran chairman rramanan ceo  md jk gupta cfo services it business consulting and outsourcing services revenue ₹ million us million  net income ₹ million us million  profit after tax number of employees   parent tata consultancy services website wwwcmcltdcom cmc limited was an information technology services consulting and software company having its headquarters in new delhi india cmc is part of the tata group and is owned by tata consultancy services cmc was incorporated on  december  as the computer management corporation private limited the government of india held  per cent of the equity share capital and owned by government of india on  august  it was converted into a public limited company in october  cmc was privatized by the government of india in a sale to indiabased tata consultancy services tcs the largest software services company in asia it also features on top ten companies in india historyedit during the year india cmc took over the maintenance of ibm installations at over  around india and subsequently maintenance of computers supplied by other foreign players cmc anticipated the market demand for it system improvements in  and directed its efforts to respond to the governments activities and needs for such services project interact international education and research for applications of computer technology a united nations project involving design development and systemsengineering computerbased systems applications in the areas of power distribution railway freight operations management and meteorology transitioned the company from a hardware maintenance company to a broad it solutions providercitation needed cmc later expanded its services to systems integration interfacing installation commissioning software development as well as education and training cmcs rd facility was set up in  at hyderabad cmc was renamed cmc limited computer maintenance corporation in august citation needed cmc limited has the credit of introducing computer applications at a mass scale in the late s with its design and deployment of indian railways reservation system impress integrated multitrain passenger reservation system in new delhi on  october  it went on to become a huge success eventually deployed all over india serving over half a million transactions every single day and cutting wait times for passengers drastically cmc also followed it up with the design of arts advanced railway ticketing system for unreserved ticketing following a spurt in the global demand for it services in the early s particularly in the united states cmc decided to expand its operations and market its product and service offerings in these markets towards this end in  cmc acquired baton rouge international inc usa it was subsequently renamed cmc americas inc in  one of the first crossborder acquisitions by an indian it firm in  the indian government divested  per cent of cmcs equity to the general insurance corporation of india and its subsidiaries who in turn sold part of their stake to the public in  in  cmcs shares were listed on the hyderabad stock exchange and the bombay stock exchange bse to service and develop its clientele in the uk and europe cmc opened a branch office in london in  the next year the government divested  per cent of cmcs equity to tata sons ltd through a strategic sale and cmc became a part of the tata group in line with its strategy of offering its products and services globally in  cmc opened a branch office in dubai to tap the hitherto unexplored markets of west asia and africa in  the government divested its remaining  per cent stake in cmc to the public the board of directors of cmc decided to merge the company into its parent company tata consultancy services limited on   october   cmc merged with tcs on  october  referencesedit  a b cmc — contact us cmcltdcom retrieved  february    cmc  about us  corporate profile — your it partner cmcltdcom retrieved  august    latest stockshare market updates  corporate news  announcements  bse bseindiacom retrieved on  september   cmc  about us  fact file — cmc — an overview cmcltdcom retrieved  august    tata group  our businesses  tata companies  cmc tataco